06485nam a22007095i 9780773571181DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20032003xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735711817 a10.1515/97807735711812doi  a(DE-B1597)654922  a(OCoLC)80221051  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aR726.5bE465 2003eb 7aMED0000002bisacsh04a610.69/61 aDubé, Laurette, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aEmotional and Interpersonal Dimensions of Health Services :bEnriching the Art of Care with the Science of Care /cLaurette Dubé, 0 Moskowitz, Guylaine Ferland. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[2003] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (232 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tIntegrating the Art and Science of Care into the Everyday Delivery of Health Services: Challenges for Research and Practice -- tMeasuring the Quality of the Primary Care Relationship -- tThe Emotional and Interpersonal Dimensions of Health Care and Their Impact on Organizational and Clinical Outcomes: Building an Integrative, Action-Oriented Research Agenda -- tMeasuring and Monitoring Patient Outcomes -- tBehind Every Great Caregiver: The Emotional Labour in Health Care -- tPatient Emotions in a Clinical Context: Coping with Anxiety and Depression and Other Negative Emotions -- tPatient Emotions and the “Engineering” of Provider Responses for More Effective Care -- tInterpersonal Process in the Patient-Physician Relationship -- tPatient-Practitioner Communication in Conventional and Complementary Medicine Contexts -- tAn Interpersonal Social Support Approach to Understanding the Patient-Practitioner Relationship -- tDynamic Conceptions of Dimensions in the Interpersonal Domain -- tMethodological Challenges to Capturing Dynamical Aspects of Health Care Acquisition -- tOutcomes in Health Care: Motivation, Measures, and Drivers at the Population Level -- tReferences -- tContributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aContributors examine the degree to which the provision of health care is influenced by characteristics of the health service organization, such as the administrative structure and the human resources available. They demonstrate that job satisfaction and conditions play an important role in shaping the quality and effectiveness of care and discuss the emotional support health care providers need to avoid long-term exhaustion and ensure well being. The contributors identify qualities of the client-provider interaction that lead to positive health care outcomes, such as providing information, responding to patient concerns, facilitating interactions with the health care system, and encouraging participation in personal health care and offer examples of innovative conceptual and analytical approaches to better health care practices. Contributors include Heather Boon (University of Toronto), Laurette Dubé, Carole A. Estabrooks (University of Alberta), Guylaine Ferland, Arlie Russell Hochschild (University of California, Berkley), Diane M. Irvine Doran (University of Toronto), Terrence Montague (Merck Frosst Canada), D.S. Moskowitz, Richard W.J. Neufeld (University of Western Ontario), Gilbert Pinard (McGill University), Debra L. Roter (John Hopkins Blooomberg School of Public Health), Dana Gelb Safran (New England Medical Center), and Krista K. Trobst (York University).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh1 aBoon, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubé, Laurette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEstabrooks, Carole A., econtributor